1
00:00:00,430 --> 00:00:02,029
Oh Jahyeon and Tak Sungwoong

2
00:00:02,270 --> 00:00:05,090
have a son.

3
00:00:08,820 --> 00:00:10,130
Mr. Ju.

4
00:00:10,550 --> 00:00:11,870
That Granny Park,

5
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:15,510
wasn't she Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN?

6
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:16,900
So?

7
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:19,090
What if she wasn't just her OB-GYN,

8
00:00:19,180 --> 00:00:21,250
but the one who delivered her son?

9
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,900
[Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN]

10
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,820
Go on.

11
00:00:24,010 --> 00:00:27,370
If her husband found out
she had an love child

12
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:26,860
[Oh Jahyeon's husband, Kwak Seunghwan]

13
00:00:27,130 --> 00:00:29,700
[Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN]

14
00:00:27,550 --> 00:00:31,180
and went to this retired OB-GYN
to verify it,

15
00:00:31,770 --> 00:00:33,430
it explains why these two died

16
00:00:33,460 --> 00:00:34,990
within 3 days of each other.

17
00:00:35,020 --> 00:00:38,220
Since my dad stated in his will that

18
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:40,170
if she had any ties with that man,

19
00:00:40,230 --> 00:00:42,430
she'd be removed from the inheritance.

20
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:44,570
And at risk of being removed

21
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,300
from the inheritance,

22
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:47,240
[Oh Jahyeon's husband, Kwak Seunghwan]

23
00:00:46,450 --> 00:00:49,920
she had no choice but to kill
everyone who knew the secret.

24
00:00:47,310 --> 00:00:48,250
[Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN]

25
00:00:51,090 --> 00:00:53,260
The arrest warrant for Oh Jahyeon
has been approved, right?

26
00:00:53,260 --> 00:00:57,520
Yes, her lawyer has contacted to say
that she will appear for interrogation.

27
00:01:01,870 --> 00:01:02,810
I don't know.

28
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:05,420
How many times must I say I don't know?

29
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,810
Are you deaf?

30
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:11,110
No matter what you ask,
I don't know anything.

31
00:01:27,140 --> 00:01:31,010
Why don't we bring up
her son with Director Tak?

32
00:01:31,220 --> 00:01:32,960
That might get her to talk.

33
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,640
Not yet. If we do that,

34
00:01:35,940 --> 00:01:38,870
Tak Sungwoong will end up
taking all the blame alone.

35
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,250
Ugh, damn it.

36
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:50,370
Prosecutor Ju.

37
00:01:52,539 --> 00:01:55,080
Can I smoke in here?

38
00:02:13,110 --> 00:02:14,800
It's on me!

39
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:16,570
Pick as many as you want.

40
00:02:17,329 --> 00:02:18,740
Thank you.

41
00:02:32,310 --> 00:02:34,120
So, has Oh Jahyeon confessed?

42
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:35,900
No.

43
00:02:36,329 --> 00:02:39,030
She has to answer something before we can
even run a polygraph or something.

44
00:02:39,030 --> 00:02:40,490
Even if she gets locked up,

45
00:02:40,770 --> 00:02:42,880
as the heiress of Ohsong Group,

46
00:02:43,010 --> 00:02:44,610
she'll be out soon anyway.

47
00:02:45,350 --> 00:02:46,790
I doubt it.

48
00:02:47,110 --> 00:02:48,200
Why?

49
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:51,370
Did you find anything else
besides the drugs?

50
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:05,720
Oh Jahyeon and Tak Sungwoong have a son.

51
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:08,790
Their son's DNA was found
at the body dumping site.

52
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,240
No, wait.

53
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:12,460
They even have a son?

54
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:15,130
What a headache.

55
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:18,250
Director Tak being involved
is troublesome enough.

56
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:19,790
Hey, Ju.

57
00:03:19,930 --> 00:03:23,190
I only took this case because
I thought it was about Ohsong Group.

58
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:24,300
What,

59
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:27,650
were you planning to score big
and move up in the world?

60
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,190
Seriously.

61
00:03:29,940 --> 00:03:31,420
Why ask the obvious?

62
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,420
Can't we hold off on that arrest warrant

63
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:34,930
and investigate without detention?

64
00:03:34,930 --> 00:03:37,780
We might get labeled as
a traitor going after our own.

65
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:40,310
As you said, they're our own.

66
00:03:40,510 --> 00:03:43,240
There's a real risk of
evidence being destroyed.

67
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:47,800
Gosh, I feel so hurt.

68
00:03:48,060 --> 00:03:49,850
Are you hiding something from me?

69
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:51,390
What? No.

70
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:54,170
We just haven't made any headway.

71
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:56,250
Fine.

72
00:03:56,650 --> 00:03:58,250
Hey, stop excluding me.

73
00:03:58,579 --> 00:03:59,750
You and Mr. Ju are basically

74
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:02,280
joined at the hip.
What are you even busy with?

75
00:04:02,460 --> 00:04:03,640
Are you two dating?

76
00:04:04,020 --> 00:04:05,430
What?

77
00:04:05,630 --> 00:04:08,160
I hate office romances the most!

78
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:11,020
What do you mean "dating"...

79
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,940
Woah, Mr. Lee,

80
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,360
are you dating a colleague?

81
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,460
Who is it?

82
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:17,310
No way.

83
00:04:17,490 --> 00:04:20,269
No one in our office
has time to date anyway.

84
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,920
We're so swamped.

85
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,360
Yeah, Ju, take it easy.

86
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:26,710
If you want to work hard, do it yourself.

87
00:04:29,490 --> 00:04:31,400
Mr. Ju, I'll head up first.

88
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,470
I'll see you
at the interrogation room later.

89
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:38,040
Thanks for the drink, Mr. Song!

90
00:04:38,260 --> 00:04:39,190
No problem!

91
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:58,670
Didn't your parents teach you

92
00:04:58,670 --> 00:05:01,020
not to take food from strangers?

93
00:05:01,370 --> 00:05:04,110
Mr. Song isn't a stranger.

94
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:05,350
Right.

95
00:05:05,770 --> 00:05:07,840
You two even went on a date once.

96
00:05:07,970 --> 00:05:09,220
I-I did not!

97
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:11,950
You say you hate office romances,

98
00:05:12,210 --> 00:05:15,270
but here you are,
two-timing in a prosecutor's office?

99
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,410
I told you you've got it wrong!

100
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,030
Then when are we going on a date?

101
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:32,180
Oh, Mr. Ju.

102
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:35,470
Trying to change the subject
to avoid answering me, huh?

103
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:37,070
No,

104
00:05:37,230 --> 00:05:38,630
Oh Jahyeon is over there.

105
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:44,480
What about her?

106
00:05:47,730 --> 00:05:49,320
She's smoking.

107
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:50,980
So what?

108
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:53,310
She asked for permission to smoke.

109
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:55,409
She vapes.

110
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,540
[Park Siwoo]

111
00:06:24,910 --> 00:06:27,750
[Kim Yunsik]

112
00:06:32,580 --> 00:06:34,260
[Kwak Seunghwan]
[Because of inheritance?]

113
00:06:34,780 --> 00:06:36,570
[Kim (Koryoin): drug overdose]

114
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,390
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

115
00:06:38,550 --> 00:06:40,580
[Last abandoned mine in Danhyeon
to be converted into a casino...]

116
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,300
[Danhyeon Land construction led by Ohsong:
casino, hotel, theme park, resort...]

117
00:06:43,450 --> 00:06:45,750
[First female executive
in the casino industry...]

118
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:48,050
[Promises "transparent management
and regional win-win"]

119
00:06:48,170 --> 00:06:49,890
[Danhyeon City "Casino Owner Murdered";
his driver, Lee, a suspect]

120
00:06:56,330 --> 00:06:58,700
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

121
00:07:03,450 --> 00:07:05,050
Even if that Koryoin, Kim,

122
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:07,710
inhaled an excessive amount
of smoke at once,

123
00:07:07,850 --> 00:07:10,370
the nicotine level in his blood
couldn't be that high.

124
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:13,810
But it's a different story
if pure nicotine was injected directly.

125
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:16,890
What if the nicotine was put in a syringe
and injected into his neck?

126
00:07:16,890 --> 00:07:20,220
The nicotine level in his blood
would spike instantly.

127
00:07:21,790 --> 00:07:22,930
That explains

128
00:07:23,690 --> 00:07:25,930
the syringe needle mark on his neck

129
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:28,220
and the high nicotine level.

130
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,730
Good job, Mr. Lee.

131
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:39,670
Let me go provoke that hothead.

132
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,430
Do you know who this is?

133
00:08:03,370 --> 00:08:04,670
It's a dead body.

134
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:13,200
How do you think he died?

135
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:16,200
If I could tell
just by looking at a photo,

136
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:18,010
I wouldn't be sitting here...

137
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,850
but in your seat.

138
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:26,080
Oh Jahyeon.

139
00:08:27,260 --> 00:08:29,420
Have you ever done drugs?

140
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,590
Yup.

141
00:08:31,570 --> 00:08:34,610
Did you buy drugs from
Kim, the Koryoin drug dealer

142
00:08:34,909 --> 00:08:36,799
from Russia?

143
00:08:36,929 --> 00:08:38,320
No.

144
00:08:40,070 --> 00:08:41,309
It's a lie.

145
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:47,540
We detected a high level of nicotine
in Kim's body.

146
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:51,400
You'd have to smoke five packs in a row
to even come close this level.

147
00:08:53,820 --> 00:08:56,040
Did you stab Kim's neck

148
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:59,380
with a nicotine-filled syringe?

149
00:09:00,590 --> 00:09:03,570
Are you saying I killed him?

150
00:09:03,850 --> 00:09:06,400
That would be great if it were true,

151
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:08,310
but unfortunately, it's not.

152
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,170
Kim's cause of death

153
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:12,640
wasn't nicotine poisoning,

154
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:17,180
but a ruptured meth bag in his stomach.

155
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:29,130
But what if

156
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,690
someone stabbed Kim in the neck

157
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:32,980
with a nicotine-filled syringe

158
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,630
and mistakenly thought they killed him?

159
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:38,580
Why are you asking me this?

160
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:40,770
Did you dump Kim's body?

161
00:09:40,930 --> 00:09:42,110
No.

162
00:09:43,130 --> 00:09:44,130
Lie.

163
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:46,960
Your husband, Kwak Seunghwan,
died seven years ago.

164
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,710
Did he die of illness?

165
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:49,720
Why do you ask?

166
00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:52,120
Please answer with a simple "yes" or "no."

167
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,550
Did he die of illness?

168
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,460
Yeah.

169
00:09:57,670 --> 00:10:00,340
Was the cause of death cardiac arrest?

170
00:10:00,570 --> 00:10:01,680
Yeah.

171
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:03,050
Are you aware that

172
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:06,640
your former OB-GYN died three days later?

173
00:10:06,830 --> 00:10:07,850
No.

174
00:10:08,070 --> 00:10:12,630
Did your OB-GYN know
the truth you wanted to hide?

175
00:10:12,830 --> 00:10:14,070
No.

176
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:16,410
All lies.

177
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:19,020
The circumstantial evidence is solid.

178
00:10:31,730 --> 00:10:35,970
You neither killed
this Russian drug dealer

179
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,500
nor did you dump the body.

180
00:10:37,630 --> 00:10:39,930
I believe what you say. Why?

181
00:10:40,050 --> 00:10:41,380
Because it's the truth.

182
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,440
This drug dealer died

183
00:10:43,860 --> 00:10:47,550
because of
a ruptured meth bag in his stomach.

184
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,660
And the person who dumped the body

185
00:10:50,930 --> 00:10:52,610
was your son.

186
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,280
Son?

187
00:10:55,660 --> 00:10:57,230
What son?

188
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:58,820
Who else?

189
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:00,690
Your son, of course.

190
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:04,680
Oh Jahyeon doesn't have a son.

191
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:08,310
So the son who helped dump the body
isn't a son?

192
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,600
What the hell are you talking about?

193
00:11:12,330 --> 00:11:14,660
The chairman would be thrilled if he knew.

194
00:11:14,710 --> 00:11:17,330
Or maybe he'd find it troublesome,

195
00:11:17,690 --> 00:11:19,950
since he'd have to rewrite his will.

196
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:24,150
Now you're just making things up,
you bastard.

197
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:26,270
I'm the casino director,

198
00:11:26,430 --> 00:11:28,520
and a member of
the family that runs Ohsung.

199
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:31,830
If I had a child,
the whole world would know.

200
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:35,300
Why are you rattling on
like you know anything?

201
00:11:35,430 --> 00:11:36,850
Yes, exactly.

202
00:11:36,970 --> 00:11:39,230
If the son were yours and your husband's,

203
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,810
the whole world would know.

204
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:54,390
Is this man... the father of your son?

205
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:56,040
Screw you!

206
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:57,580
Stop with this load of bull!

207
00:11:57,580 --> 00:12:00,810
If it's just bull, why are you so angry?

208
00:12:01,830 --> 00:12:03,510
Say one more word,

209
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,270
and I'll rip your mouth off.

210
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:07,760
Seven years ago,

211
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:10,600
your husband died for no reason.

212
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:14,270
Three days later,
your retired OB-GYN was murdered.

213
00:12:14,410 --> 00:12:16,330
Now, your son's DNA

214
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:19,100
was detected at the body dumping site!

215
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,830
But you,

216
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:28,840
who doesn't have a son,

217
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:32,490
have absolutely nothing to do
with all these deaths.

218
00:12:32,630 --> 00:12:36,300
So, we just need to arrest the son
for dumping the body.

219
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:41,030
Damn you, you cocky bastard!

220
00:12:41,220 --> 00:12:43,030
-Screw you!
-Mr. Song!

221
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:43,880
Please call the guards.

222
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:44,700
Got it.

223
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:45,980
You bastard!

224
00:12:46,780 --> 00:12:49,190
Do you know what happens
when you mess with me?

225
00:12:49,190 --> 00:12:50,770
Who do you think you are, bastard!

226
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:51,400
Damn you!

227
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:52,470
Please let go. Calm down.

228
00:12:52,470 --> 00:12:53,130
Let go of me!

229
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,440
-Let go of me!
-Calm down.

230
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,620
Let go of me!

231
00:12:56,670 --> 00:12:58,890
Place her in
the district office detention cell

232
00:12:58,890 --> 00:13:01,820
for assaulting a prosecutor
during interrogation.

233
00:13:02,570 --> 00:13:05,640
You took so much of my money.
Can't you do something, you idiot?

234
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:07,420
Idiot!

235
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:12,090
I won't let you off!

236
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:15,180
Are you OK?

237
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:16,890
Please, this is nothing.

238
00:13:17,580 --> 00:13:20,450
I've even been punched by
homeless people before.

239
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:27,320
Good thing Oh Jahyeon
didn't come after you.

240
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:31,770
We have enough circumstantial evidence,
but no actual proof.

241
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:33,940
We'll have to work on finding proof now.

242
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:34,990
OK.

243
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:38,320
Without actual proof, my hands are tied;

244
00:13:38,930 --> 00:13:40,020
you know that.

245
00:13:40,030 --> 00:13:41,970
[Prosecution]

246
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:46,100
[Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]

247
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,690
[Tak Sungwoong's phone location history]

248
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:51,420
[Call Detail Record]

249
00:13:54,950 --> 00:13:56,470
[Tuesday, February 17
10:18]

250
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,570
Why are you so deep in thought?

251
00:14:30,660 --> 00:14:32,140
Oh Jahyeon...

252
00:14:35,170 --> 00:14:37,190
She looked a bit sad.

253
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,170
Why would she be sad?

254
00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:41,710
It's a love that's never meant to be.

255
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,870
She even raised a son in secret.

256
00:14:46,730 --> 00:14:49,290
Don't get emotional over this crap.

257
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:52,980
We barely have time
to figure out where the evidence is.

258
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:56,300
Yes, got it.

259
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:57,740
Let's call it a day.

260
00:14:58,020 --> 00:14:59,300
OK.

261
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,250
Today,

262
00:15:09,530 --> 00:15:11,500
should we go to your dorm?

263
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:16,000
G-Go to... my dorm?

264
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:19,230
Isn't the soundproofing bad there?

265
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:21,650
Uh,

266
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,140
yeah.

267
00:15:23,740 --> 00:15:25,030
That's great.

268
00:15:26,350 --> 00:15:28,070
Make a sound and you're dead.

269
00:15:28,490 --> 00:15:30,240
What... sound?

270
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:54,490
I said, make a sound and you're dead.

271
00:16:14,890 --> 00:16:15,830
Damn it!

272
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:25,070
What if people see you

273
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,920
frequenting my dorm and start gossiping?

274
00:16:28,290 --> 00:16:30,570
Let's just go to our own homes today...

275
00:16:30,810 --> 00:16:34,850
What's so weird about
a prosecutor visiting his investigator?

276
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,890
What exactly is going on in your head?

277
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:39,260
Besides,

278
00:16:39,470 --> 00:16:41,070
do I make you uncomfortable?

279
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,440
Not at all...

280
00:16:43,110 --> 00:16:44,830
Hello, pretty boy.

281
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:59,570
What a strong grip.

282
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:01,740
What do you want?

283
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:07,240
It's so unfair that only you guys
are prying into my secrets.

284
00:17:07,329 --> 00:17:08,069
Oh Jahyeon.

285
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,280
Hmm?

286
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,760
We're not prying into personal secrets

287
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,230
but investigating crimes.

288
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:16,200
Don't cloud the issue

289
00:17:16,329 --> 00:17:17,770
and leave.

290
00:17:23,390 --> 00:17:24,380
Let's go.

291
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:27,980
Prosecutors have to be fair.

292
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:36,710
Geez, look at that fierce stare.

293
00:17:39,780 --> 00:17:44,920
I'm going to give each of you a secret
you've been keeping from each other,

294
00:17:45,380 --> 00:17:47,240
since I'm a fair person.

295
00:17:50,850 --> 00:17:55,220
Lee Chaeha is Lee Gilyoung's son.

296
00:17:56,660 --> 00:17:58,920
Oh Jahyeon, I'm going to call for backup.

297
00:17:59,130 --> 00:18:00,550
What the hell?

298
00:18:00,910 --> 00:18:01,960
So boring.

299
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,800
You already knew?

300
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,560
Get in the car.

301
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,380
OK.

302
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:09,340
Then,

303
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:13,080
what could Ju Taeseon's secret

304
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:16,650
be?

305
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:26,420
Oh, you don't know!

306
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,020
Want to know?

307
00:18:29,220 --> 00:18:30,150
Curious, right?

308
00:18:30,410 --> 00:18:31,780
Get in the car now, Lee Chaeha.

309
00:18:31,780 --> 00:18:33,730
What are you afraid of, Taeseon?

310
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,250
Lee Chaeha!

311
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,500
Wait a minute, Mr. Ju.

312
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,590
What?

313
00:18:42,380 --> 00:18:43,850
Mr. Ju?

314
00:18:44,020 --> 00:18:45,890
Mr. Ju!

315
00:18:51,420 --> 00:18:52,840
Let's go.

316
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,930
She's out of her mind.

317
00:19:02,470 --> 00:19:03,950
Chaeha, please.

318
00:19:10,610 --> 00:19:15,570
Lee Chaeha is Lee Gilyoung's son,

319
00:19:16,330 --> 00:19:17,460
right?

320
00:19:19,310 --> 00:19:20,580
Yes.

321
00:19:36,630 --> 00:19:38,690
Son!

322
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:45,780
Then whose son could he be?

323
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:52,100
How could you not know!
You're such a fool.

324
00:19:52,470 --> 00:19:56,360
Even if others don't know,
at least you should.

325
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:57,800
Don't you think?

326
00:20:00,980 --> 00:20:05,530
Kang Taeseon.

327
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:08,670
Chaeha, don't listen.

328
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:19,000
Kang... Taeseon?

329
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,530
Yup!

330
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,800
He's Kang Taeseon.

331
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:24,550
His father is Kang Woosung.

332
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:28,430
The Kang Woosung your father killed
is his father.

333
00:20:40,330 --> 00:20:43,410
Didn't Taeseon appoint you himself?

334
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,600
Did you do it on purpose?

335
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,710
For revenge?

336
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:55,650
How does it feel?

337
00:20:57,070 --> 00:21:01,200
When you two were digging up my secrets,

338
00:21:01,330 --> 00:21:03,960
did you feel like this too?

339
00:21:06,410 --> 00:21:07,980
The son of the murderer.

340
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:10,280
The son of the victim.

341
00:21:11,970 --> 00:21:15,410
Why are you so quiet, Taeseon?

342
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:18,710
When you saw Woosung's body...

343
00:21:19,710 --> 00:21:22,080
did you have this look on your face too?

344
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:26,430
You were speechless back then, too.

345
00:21:26,690 --> 00:21:28,640
You coward.

346
00:21:45,560 --> 00:21:46,970
Lee Chaeha.

347
00:21:50,570 --> 00:21:51,830
Chaeha!

348
00:22:08,830 --> 00:22:11,580
Did you think changing your surname

349
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:14,920
could hide the fact that
you're Kang Woosung's son?

350
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,060
Neither Lee Chaeha nor you

351
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:20,960
can ever escape
the shadows of your fathers.

352
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:24,090
We all knew all along!

353
00:22:34,460 --> 00:22:36,580
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

354
00:22:36,590 --> 00:22:39,670
[In the Next Episode]

355
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,540
Now, just looking at your face

356
00:22:38,650 --> 00:22:40,760
makes me feel wretched and miserable.

357
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,030
Is this what you want?

358
00:22:47,090 --> 00:22:48,950
-Let's talk when we get back.
-OK.

359
00:22:52,130 --> 00:22:54,490
I'm afraid Mr. Lee will be disciplined.

360
00:22:54,830 --> 00:22:55,520
What?

361
00:22:55,660 --> 00:22:59,550
Why is it that the more miserable you are,
the more miserable I become?

362
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:03,110
Chaeha, I'm sorry. It was my fault.

363
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:06,120
This isn't some final goodbye, is it?

364
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:12,510
[Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]

365
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:08,850
Hello?

366
00:23:09,030 --> 00:23:09,800
Lee Chaeha?

367
00:23:09,980 --> 00:23:10,970
Chaeha.

